{% set basicCode %}<print-page>Print this page</print-page>{% endset %}

{% set toggleCode %}<!-- With checkbox to disable VB print optimizations -->
<print-page data-raw-toggle>Print this page</print-page>{% endset %}

{% set labelCode %}<print-page data-label="Save as PDF"></print-page>{% endset %}

{% set inContextCode %}<article>
  <h1>Quarterly Report</h1>
  <p>...</p>

  <footer>
    <print-page data-raw-toggle data-no-print>Print report</print-page>
  </footer>
</article>{% endset %}

<section>
  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>The <code>&lt;print-page&gt;</code> component wraps <code>window.print()</code> in a progressive enhancement button. It auto-hides itself when printing and optionally lets users toggle VB&rsquo;s print style optimizations on or off.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Basic print button">{{ basicCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>Without JavaScript, the element renders as inert text. With JavaScript, it becomes a functional print button.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Attributes</h2>
  <table class="props-table">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Attribute</th>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th>Default</th>
        <th>Description</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-raw-toggle</code></td>
        <td>Boolean</td>
        <td>&mdash;</td>
        <td>If present, shows a checkbox labeled &ldquo;Print without VB styles&rdquo;</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-label</code></td>
        <td>String</td>
        <td>Element text or &ldquo;Print this page&rdquo;</td>
        <td>Custom button label</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Raw Mode Toggle</h2>
  <p>When <code>data-raw-toggle</code> is present, the component adds a checkbox. If checked, it sets <code>data-print-raw</code> on the <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> element before opening the print dialog, which disables all VB print optimizations. The attribute is removed after printing.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="With raw-mode toggle">{{ toggleCode | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>This is useful for users who want to see the page print exactly as it appears on screen &mdash; with theme colors, shadows, and layout intact.</p>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Custom Label</h2>
  <p>Set the button text via <code>data-label</code> or as the element&rsquo;s text content.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Custom label">{{ labelCode | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Usage in Context</h2>
  <p>Place the component wherever makes sense. It hides itself during printing automatically. Adding <code>data-no-print</code> is redundant but makes intent explicit.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Typical placement">{{ inContextCode | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

